00:52:47.610 --> 00:52:51.005
So what kind of changes
would you make, if

00:52:51.005 --> 00:52:53.080
you were the dictator?

00:52:53.080 --> 00:52:54.245
OZZIE ZEHNER: Whew, well--

00:52:54.245 --> 00:52:55.495
AUDIENCE: Sorry, loaded.

00:52:58.280 --> 00:52:59.980
OZZIE ZEHNER: First of all,
there would be Lucky Charms in

00:52:59.980 --> 00:53:01.230
all of the restaurants.

00:53:03.740 --> 00:53:10.270
I think probably universal
health care would be the

00:53:10.270 --> 00:53:11.640
number one priority.

00:53:11.640 --> 00:53:14.870
I feel like universal health
care has so many benefits.

00:53:14.870 --> 00:53:18.420
And we often hear people say oh,
I don't really want to pay

00:53:18.420 --> 00:53:19.900
for that person's health care.

00:53:19.900 --> 00:53:22.695
And it's just like that person
is going to go to

00:53:22.695 --> 00:53:24.300
the doctor too much.

00:53:24.300 --> 00:53:26.700
Well, first of all that kind of
like a remarkable breakdown

00:53:26.700 --> 00:53:27.960
in civil society.

00:53:27.960 --> 00:53:31.250
It represents a kind of
remarkable drawback from that

00:53:31.250 --> 00:53:33.150
perspective.

00:53:33.150 --> 00:53:36.010
But also, most people don't
recognize that we already have

00:53:36.010 --> 00:53:37.860
an emergency universal
health care system

00:53:37.860 --> 00:53:38.630
in the United States.

00:53:38.630 --> 00:53:42.640
When a homeless person goes
into the ER with pneumonia

00:53:42.640 --> 00:53:46.690
because they didn't have health
care, they end up

00:53:46.690 --> 00:53:49.410
spending a lot of money
on bringing that

00:53:49.410 --> 00:53:50.390
person back to health.

00:53:50.390 --> 00:53:54.070
And of course, that system
is incredibly expensive.

00:53:54.070 --> 00:53:55.890
And that's why we could actually
save money by going

00:53:55.890 --> 00:53:58.160
to something like a universal
health care system, like the

00:53:58.160 --> 00:53:58.650
ones in Europe.

00:53:58.650 --> 00:54:01.080
And there's nothing
about the health

00:54:01.080 --> 00:54:02.740
care systems in Europe--

00:54:02.740 --> 00:54:05.190
they're not perfect, I guess
is what I'm trying to say.

00:54:05.190 --> 00:54:08.535
But you also don't see Germans
in the streets protesting for

00:54:08.535 --> 00:54:10.120
an American style health
care system.

00:54:12.930 --> 00:54:15.630
And I think that's something we
have to keep in mind too,

00:54:15.630 --> 00:54:19.300
in all the rhetoric going back
and forth on these issues.

00:54:19.300 --> 00:54:23.690
The other things that I would
enable, to make a short list,

00:54:23.690 --> 00:54:25.800
