00:55:32.460 --> 00:55:36.940
like for India as country, the
population has been mostly

00:55:36.940 --> 00:55:39.950
huge for thousands of years.

00:55:39.950 --> 00:55:43.150
And I usually read a lot of
Sanskrit literature from

00:55:43.150 --> 00:55:46.250
ancient stories, like ancient
history of India.

00:55:46.250 --> 00:55:49.910
It's been a vast population
all the time.

00:55:49.910 --> 00:55:51.510
And it's been sustaining.

00:55:51.510 --> 00:55:54.910
All the problems that you
mention having to do with

00:55:54.910 --> 00:55:58.590
electricity and fossil fuels,
that all started like in only

00:55:58.590 --> 00:56:01.030
the last 100 years or so.

00:56:01.030 --> 00:56:03.910
But prior to that danger,
civilization has been running

00:56:03.910 --> 00:56:07.700
for years and years and years
without any of these problems.

00:56:07.700 --> 00:56:10.290
So I'd just like to point out
that it's not necessarily the

00:56:10.290 --> 00:56:11.300
population.

00:56:11.300 --> 00:56:14.560
But it's under a dimension that
I would like to just kind

00:56:14.560 --> 00:56:17.030
of hint at here, which you
might be interested in

00:56:17.030 --> 00:56:21.670
pursuing for further, which
is actually the concept of

00:56:21.670 --> 00:56:24.600
consciousness, like
who we really are.

00:56:24.600 --> 00:56:28.360
What bring satisfaction to us as
a person, as a individual.

00:56:28.360 --> 00:56:32.170
So the Indian culture is kind
of focused on that spiritual

00:56:32.170 --> 00:56:35.880
dimension, which provides the
higher level of satisfaction

00:56:35.880 --> 00:56:38.010
so that you don't depend
on gadgets and material

00:56:38.010 --> 00:56:41.100
technology to fulfill your
demands constantly.

00:56:41.100 --> 00:56:44.120
Which is what that the vast
majority of the consumption

00:56:44.120 --> 00:56:44.950
comes from.

00:56:44.950 --> 00:56:49.380
So without providing an
ultimate higher way of

00:56:49.380 --> 00:56:52.170
enjoying your life, you cannot
really take away all the

00:56:52.170 --> 00:56:54.680
gadgets and say that
be [INAUDIBLE]

00:56:54.680 --> 00:56:57.760
and solve the energy
problem that way.

00:56:57.760 --> 00:57:01.090
Rather, the Indian culture is
focused on the aspect that

00:57:01.090 --> 00:57:04.870
you're a spiritual being and you
can be satisfied by other

00:57:04.870 --> 00:57:10.300
means spiritually, compared
to you using gadgets.

00:57:10.300 --> 00:57:13.300
That's one of the main reasons
that civilization has

00:57:13.300 --> 00:57:15.320
sustained for so many years.

00:57:15.320 --> 00:57:19.410
So I'd just like to comment on
that and see if you have any

00:57:19.410 --> 00:57:20.900
thoughts about that?

00:57:20.900 --> 00:57:23.540
OZZIE ZEHNER: Well, I should
make a clarification that

00:57:23.540 --> 00:57:28.330
probably our views are not
incongruent, in that I'm not

00:57:28.330 --> 00:57:30.150
for population control.

00:57:30.150 --> 00:57:31.710
I should say that right
off the bat.

00:57:31.710 --> 00:57:35.190
In fact, I think the idea of
population control within the

00:57:35.190 --> 00:57:37.160
environmental movement, and
there are some people pushing

00:57:37.160 --> 00:57:39.220
for population control,
and I think

00:57:39.220 --> 00:57:40.940
that's a misguided effort.

00:57:40.940 --> 00:57:46.100
And that's because I do think it
tramples on the ability for

00:57:46.100 --> 00:57:50.870
societies and for individuals
to have a free life and

00:57:50.870 --> 00:57:52.400
procreate how they choose to.

00:57:52.400 --> 00:57:55.140
But we find that actually
coercion is not

00:57:55.140 --> 00:57:57.260
necessary at all.

00:57:57.260 --> 00:57:59.880
If you look in China, the lowest
birth rate is in a

00:57:59.880 --> 00:58:01.780
place where the one-child
policy does not

00:58:01.780 --> 00:58:03.640
apply, in Hong Kong.

00:58:03.640 --> 00:58:06.990
And we find that throughout
the world.

00:58:06.990 --> 00:58:08.930
Actually Shanghai, also.

00:58:08.930 --> 00:58:12.570
It doesn't apply and Shanghai
also has a low birth rate.

00:58:12.570 --> 00:58:15.830
We find that really by just
instituting human rights and

00:58:15.830 --> 00:58:18.750
health care, it allows people to
have the number of children

00:58:18.750 --> 00:58:19.860
that they want to have.

00:58:19.860 --> 00:58:23.130
And that number happens
to be sustainable

00:58:23.130 --> 00:58:24.520
over the long term.

00:58:24.520 --> 00:58:28.010
And so really the trick I think
is just delivering human

00:58:28.010 --> 00:58:29.590
rights and health care
in the first place.

00:58:29.590 --> 00:58:34.240
I really see population growth
as a symptom of suboptimal

00:58:34.240 --> 00:58:35.430
social conditions.

00:58:35.430 --> 00:58:39.320
So the real thing to do is to
just satisfy those social

00:58:39.320 --> 00:58:41.340
conditions and the population
growth will

00:58:41.340 --> 00:58:42.050
take care of itself.

