01:01:35.550 --> 01:01:40.700
But nuclear is a fascinating
case because it is something

01:01:40.700 --> 01:01:43.100
that is actually scalable and
there is a lot of fissionable

01:01:43.100 --> 01:01:44.220
material on the planet.

01:01:44.220 --> 01:01:46.890
And that can be looked at as
a blessing or a curse.

01:01:46.890 --> 01:01:51.150
And there's people that look
at it from both directions.

01:01:51.150 --> 01:01:53.440
The issue with nuclear power
is that we have yet another

01:01:53.440 --> 01:01:56.990
set of side effects and
limitations and consequences.

01:01:56.990 --> 01:01:58.430
Some of them, we
know very well.

01:01:58.430 --> 01:02:01.855
Some of them are risky
situations, that are growing

01:02:01.855 --> 01:02:05.110
and accumulating over time,
such as that with waste

01:02:05.110 --> 01:02:08.530
disposal and access
to proliferating

01:02:08.530 --> 01:02:10.120
materials like plutonium.

01:02:10.120 --> 01:02:15.140
And the nuclear armaments
industry has even tested

01:02:15.140 --> 01:02:19.110
byproducts from the thorium
cycle in anticipation that

01:02:19.110 --> 01:02:20.720
there might be a thorium
push in the future.

01:02:20.720 --> 01:02:23.650
So we will look at conflict.

01:02:23.650 --> 01:02:26.690
We look at potential for
materials getting diverted.

01:02:26.690 --> 01:02:29.460
We look at long term storage
of nuclear waste.

01:02:29.460 --> 01:02:32.940
We look at the potential
for explosions or

01:02:32.940 --> 01:02:34.890
like Fukushima disasters.

01:02:34.890 --> 01:02:37.040
And so, we just get another
set of side

01:02:37.040 --> 01:02:38.140
effects with nuclear.

01:02:38.140 --> 01:02:41.570
But the big issue with nuclear
that shouldn't be

01:02:41.570 --> 01:02:43.880
underestimated is that there
is a lot of fissionable

01:02:43.880 --> 01:02:45.040
material on the planet.

01:02:45.040 --> 01:02:49.680
And we're going to run into
different types of barriers

01:02:49.680 --> 01:02:50.970
with nuclear than we're

01:02:50.970 --> 01:02:52.732
encountering with fossil fuels.

